                    "description": "Since my retirement from CHEPS I have been involved in various activities such as editorial work and reviewing of book and articles, as well as consultancy on labour market policies in Saudi Arabia, issues on higher vocational education and qualification frameworks with presentations in Kyrgyzstan (Central Asian Education Platform -CAEP) and at Kyushu University, Japan. \n\nCurrently member of  the advisory board (Wissenschaftlicher Beirat) for the Research Project \u201cKarrieren Promovierter\u201d (Promovierten-Panel) by the \"Zentrum f\u00fcr Hochschul- und Wissenschaftsforschung\", DZHW) in Hannover, Germany. This project investigates the impact of the formal promotionscontext and conditions for the further career of doctoral students both inside and outside academia. The model includes dimensions of the \u201cLernumweltkonzept\u201d: degree of structuration of doctoral programmes, support, challenge and orientation. The project will continue in 2018. For more info:  www.promoviertenpanel.de/",
